# Git...

  <pr>Git is a free, open-source software tool that tracks changes in your files. It acts like a powerful "undo" history for your code, helping you collaborate seamlessly with other developers.<pr>

# Core Concepts:-

 <pr> To understand Git, picture your project progressing along a timeline.The Standard Git WorkflowMost developers use Git by following these four basic steps:<pr>

__Modify__: Edit, delete, or create files in your project folder.
<br>
__Stage__: Run git add <filename> to move files into the staging area.
<br>
__Commit__: Run git commit -m "Your message" to permanently save that snapshot.
<br>
__Push__: Run git push to upload your local commits to a remote server like GitHub.